{
  "_README": [
    "Phase 1 address table for generate-phase1-batches.ts.",
    "",
    "PURPOSE: redeploy MagnetaOFTStandardFactory on each LZ-V2 chain and re-wire it so",
    "(a) newly-created tokens auto-register on the local TokenOpsModule (the registerToken",
    "functional fix), and (b) cross-chain CREATE_TOKEN lands on the NEW factory.",
    "",
    "HOW TO USE:",
    "  1. cp phase1-addresses.template.json phase1-addresses.json",
    "  2. Deploy the new factory per chain (scripts/deploy-oft-factories.ts or redeploy-oft-std-factory.ts).",
    "     Right after deploy the factory is owned by the DEPLOYER EOA (see deploy-oft-factories.ts).",
    "  3. Fill 'newStandardFactory' (the address just deployed) and 'tokenOpsModule'",
    "     (local TokenOpsModule, = gatewayChains.ts tokenOpsModule for that chainId) per chain.",
    "  4. Decide ownership model per chain via 'factoryOwnedBySafe':",
    "       false (default) -> factory still owned by deployer EOA. The two factory setters",
    "                          (setTokenOpsModule, setCrossChainCreator) are emitted as EOA",
    "                          cast/hardhat commands (NOT in the Safe batch). Only the",
    "                          dispatcher.setStandardFactory call(s) go in the Safe batch.",
    "       true            -> you transferred factory ownership to the Safe (factory uses OZ",
    "                          4.x Ownable, single-step transferOwnership, no acceptOwnership).",
    "                          All wiring calls go in the Safe batch.",
    "  5. Run: npx hardhat run scripts/safe/generate-phase1-batches.ts",
    "     (it reads phase1-addresses.json; falls back to this template if that is absent).",
    "",
    "Addresses left blank/zero are SKIPPED (lets you generate a partial set as you fill chains).",
    "'safe', 'dispatcher', 'dispatcherV3' are pre-filled from deployments-dispatcher[-v3]/<net>.json",
    "(source of truth). Verify them before signing. Cronos (25) is excluded: no LZ V2."
  ],
